🎉 Celebrating 2 Years of Design Excellence with Kosta! 🚀

Today, we raise a toast to @kostacana as he marks his impressive 2-year work anniversary as the Lead Web UX/UI Designer at Illuvium 🎨

In these two years, Kosta's creative vision and design expertise have been instrumental in shaping the visual identity of Illuvium's online presence. His commitment to seamless user experiences and design solutions has greatly enhanced our digital landscape. Thank you for all your hard work, Kosta!

Here is what Kosta has to say about his 2 years at Illuvium:

"Two incredible years at Illuvium have flown by, but it feels like we're just warming up. Collaborating with such a skilled and passionate team, united by a singular vision, has been the adventure of a lifetime. Here's to the journey ahead—there's so much more we're eager to achieve together!"

Join us in congratulating Kosta's outstanding contributions, and here's to many more years of design brilliance at Illuvium! 🥳💻

#WorkAnniversary #LeadUXUIDesigner #Illuvium #DesignExcellence #CreativeLeadership

Update: 

The malicious version of the file was replaced with the genuine version at around 2:35pm CET. 

The new genuine version should be propagated soon. 

We will provide a comprehensive report as soon as it’s ready.

In the meantime, we’d like to remind the community to always Clear Sign your transactions - remember that the addresses and the information presented on your Ledger screen is the only genuine information.

If there’s a difference between the screen shown on your Ledger device and your computer/phone screen, stop that transaction immediately.

🚀 Illuvium Zero Progress Update 🚀

Rangers, it's been a minute since our last update, so we've got some juicy tidbits to share about what players have to look forward to 👇:

• Popups & Info: We've polished activity validation displays to make 'em more user-friendly.
• Android Bound: We're prepping for our Play Store debut. And don't worry; WebGL is still on track!
• In-game shop: Open beta will offer credits using fiat or crypto on Android. The choice is yours.
• Efficiency 2.0: Revamped calculations offer a smoother, more intuitive experience.
• Path Makeover: Expect a more straightforward approach to activity planning with added quality-of-life perks.
• Meet the Builders: Use credits to bring on more builders and get those buildings up faster.
• Visual Upgrades: New VFX and a zoom-out feature lets you see your entire plot.
• Soundscapes: FMOD integration is underway for an immersive audio experience.
• In the Works: From plants and podariums to backend security and holographic statues, we're on it.

Big thanks for sticking with us. More cool stuff is on the horizon for Illuvium Zero! 🎮🌟

🚨Rangers! We've pushed an update to IlluviDex, adding a feature many of you have requested! This aims to make your trading experience more interactive and negotiable. Here's how it unfolds: ⬇️ https://t.co/qt45uzFbj2

Accepting an Offer:

• Head to your Profile or the listed Asset.
• Tap on the Offers Tab.
• Slide to Received.
• Scrutinize the offer price.
• Hit Accept if you agree.

🔄 Buyers, feel free to withdraw your offer before it’s accepted. Sellers sift through and accept offers to seal the deal. Dive in, get a feel of these new features, and kickstart the bidding saga on IlluviDex! 🎮
Head to the Illuvidex NOW: https://t.co/vZGZsKcJbg

Making an Offer:

• Spot the Illuvitar or Land you aim to bid on.
• Hit 'Offer' atop the asset.
• Specify your bid amount in the displayed currency.
• Mind the Minimum Bid: 10% of the Listed price.
• Optionally set an expiry date (7 days min).

The single highest barrier to web3 adoption is often user acquisition. 

At Immutable, we’re all about breaking down barriers.

Immutable Passport is the all-in-one solution. Passport is changing the user acquisition equation by offering familiar login methods, automated wallet creation, and streamlined user experiences. 

https://t.co/4rRRbpvM8I

📜 We conducted a Case Study of 7,000 gamers, split into two equal groups who were presented with the following:

Flow A: Immutable Passport creation
Flow B: Traditional email field and wallet creation process

The results?

Flow A saw over double the completion rate than Flow B. New players are twice as likely to convert with Passport than other wallets! 

The design principle behind Passport is simple: make it as easy as possible for anyone to play web3 games.

Passport provides studios with an identity AND wallet solution, all inside an onboarding experience that can be completed within 20 seconds.

With Passport, game studios can feel comfortable in knowing that they can;

✅ Drive mainstream adoption
✅ Maintain enterprise-grade security
✅ Achieve global scalability

The numbers do not lie. Immutable Passport will become the default way for players to interact with all web3 games.

🔧 Illuvium Zero Tech Update [08/14 - 08/25] 🔧

It's time for a game and tech update! 💻🎮

🌱 New Plant Gameplay: Introducing a captivating layer of gameplay with plant growth stages, offering exciting rewards. Say hello to the Podarium, a new building that adds functionality with Morphopods. It's a work in progress, but the idea is to turn plants from obstacles into opportunities. Not all features will be revealed yet, but get your farmer hats on!

🎯 Quality of Life (QoL) Goals: Matt's been busy with the "Go" feature. Wondering what to do to ace a goal? No worries – now you'll get clear indications of involved gameplay elements, thanks to UI redirection. We're fine-tuning the early game experience for new and returning players, eventually resulting in a comprehensive tutorial. We're on it, even though tutorials are tough to crack.

💼 Backend Progress: Igor's been integrating more APIs to strengthen our server authority architecture. Our focus is on creating a smooth structure for players. The backend team is expanding to ensure efficient beta shipping. I'm joining in, learning the ropes of full-stack development – a collective effort!

📱 Android Endeavors: Heading towards the Play Store for Android publishing. We've tackled the alpha's size challenges, and the beta client is on point. The initial download size is leaner, and resources will load on demand. This means a smoother experience, even for those with slower connections.

💰 Credit & Builders: Changes are coming to credit rewards and builder acquisition. Expect a more straightforward method to possess multiple builders on your plot, significantly speeding up construction. These changes are coming to other platforms, too, but the design is a work in progress.

⚙️ Tech Path: These weeks have been tech-intensive, which means fewer visual sneak peeks. But hang tight – exciting gameplay changes are brewing. Dive into deeper strategies as we level up the Illuvium experience!

Thanks for your ongoing support as we power through beta development. 🙏 Stay tuned for more tech updates coming your way!

I have been testing Illuvium Beyond Wave 2 on the Goerli Testnet for about 2 weeks now. I am about to drop my thoughts right here, you aren't going to want to miss this.

First things first, the drop rates are noticeable immediately, with standard D1sks you especially notice this with the accessories. Statistically you will get something that is T3 in every 2 D1sks. Sometimes this is an accessory and sometimes not but there's WAY LESS D1sks with 3 clown noses, thank god.

Although there are quite a few Tier 1 Illuvitars you are getting way more Tier 2 and Tier 3 Illuvitars and can complete quite a bit of the collection with 100-150 standard D1sks but the fun really comes when you get to Mega D1sks.

For anyone who enjoyed Illuvium Beyond Wave 1, you noticed just how many Mega D1sks handed you an Illuvitar Between 1250-1500. The biggest thing I noticed when participating in the testing phase for Illuvium Beyond Wave 2 was just how many Illuvitars I pulled around the 1700 mark and over 2000 power.

Not only did this feel epic with every single D1sk I obtained, because there are so many expressions, Holos and rare backgrounds I felt like I always got something that had a place in my ever expanding collection.

Ultimately in Wave 1 Standard D1sks felt really weak and like they didn't have a very strong place in Illuvium Beyond, now Standard D1sks and Mega D1sks play such different roles that the collecting game feels infinitely better and I can't wait until it drops in 6 days.

📣 Attention all new business owners! 💼🚀

It's natural to feel the urge to offer discounts when launching a new product or service. It might feel like the fastest way to attract customers and make sales. However, this strategy can lead to a challenging predicament that can be difficult to rebound from. 🚫🏷️

When you constantly discount your products or services, you inadvertently send the message that they may not be worth the full price. This, in turn, lowers your brand value and makes it challenging to charge full price in the future. 💰💸

Think about it: Would you consider buying a product at full price if you know it will be on sale next week? Probably not. And neither will your customers. 🧐

So, how can you avoid falling into the discount trap? 

1. Focus on building value 🏗️. Communicate the benefits and value of your product or service, not just the price. 

2. Improve your sales skills 💪. Practice makes perfect. The more you refine your sales techniques, the more confident you'll become in selling your product or service at full price. 

3. Stand behind your pricing 💼. Have confidence in your pricing. If you're providing a quality product or service, it's worth every penny.

And what about friends and family? Should they get a "special" discount? 

While it's wonderful to have the support of friends and family, remember that your business is your livelihood. They should want to support you by paying full price, just like any other customer. This isn't about charity; it's about valuing your hard work and the quality you offer. 🙌

Running a business isn't a sprint; it's a marathon. And the journey to success starts with valuing your offerings appropriately. So, stay strong, trust your worth, and keep striving for greatness. 

Your business deserves it. YOU deserve it. 💎🎯

#NoDiscounts #ValueYourBusiness #Entrepreneurship #BusinessTips #NewBusinessOwners

📣Meet Plobbs, a beetle-like Morphopod from Illuvium! 🦟

Plobbs are Tier 0 Bulwark class Morphopods with a striking appearance. Its segmented body with six glowing eyes, rounded torso encased in a textured shell, and six legs make it stand out in the crowd. 🌟 https://t.co/tqEmMqQoMX

Analysis reveals that Plobbs have chemoreceptors in their eyes that can detect decay from a distance. Their maxillary palps have antibacterial secretions that can delay decay and infection within other Illuvials, and their abdomen stores pheromones that can attract others. 🧪

Intrigued? Stay tuned for more fascinating facts about the creatures of Illuvium! #Illuvium #Plobbs #Morphopods
